title: Fortios: IPSec
agents: special
catalog: network/fortigate
license: GPLv2
distribution: check_mk
description:
 This check monitors the IPSec tunnels of a Fortigate firewall.
 All tunnels are monitored by default.
 The "fortios_ipsec_check_parameters" rule can be used to configure the 
 tunnels ignored by name and remote subnet.
 A tunnel is displayed as {crit} if it is not active.


 The special agent is required for this check, 
 which can be configured via “FortiOS”.

discovery:
 One service per IPSec tunnel is created.
